English: Proceed to input the backdoor command [SPECIAL_COMMAND] in [ITEM_SERIAL]
Description: A short summary of a mission objective. "Input the backdoor command" is just a cool way to say you need to input a specific computer command in a terminal (the terminal ID will replace "[ITEM_SERIAL]".) Don't alter the "[SPECIAL_COMMAND]/[ITEM_SERIAL]" part, just put it in the gramatically correct position in the sentence.

French.Translation: Entrez la commande de backdoor [SPECIAL_COMMAND] dans le [ITEM_SERIAL].

German.Translation: Fahren Sie mit der Eingabe des Hintertür-Befehls [SPECIAL_COMMAND] in [ITEM_SERIAL] fort.

Spanish.Translation: Continúa e introduce el comando de la puerta trasera [SPECIAL_COMMAND] en [ITEM_SERIAL].

Portuguese_Brazil.Translation: Insira os dados do comando de backdoor [SPECIAL_COMMAND] em [ITEM_SERIAL].

Polish.Translation: Wprowadź polecenie uaktywnienia tylnym wejściem [SPECIAL_COMMAND] w [ITEM_SERIAL].

Japanese.Translation: バックドアコマンド [SPECIAL_COMMAND] を [ITEM_SERIAL]に入力しろ
